content.raw:
I don't have permission to push to your fork, so here's the diff of the fix that @scpeters helped me make to compile it:

```
diff -r 4976671759eb CMakeLists.txt
--- a/CMakeLists.txt	Tue Apr 28 14:24:39 2015 -0700
+++ b/CMakeLists.txt	Thu Apr 30 10:56:25 2015 -0700
@@ -155,7 +155,10 @@
 # uppercase old supported and deprecated modes
 string(TOUPPER ${CMAKE_BUILD_TYPE} CMAKE_BUILD_TYPE_UPPERCASE)
 
-set (HDF5_INSTRUMENT FALSE)
+if (NOT DEFINED HDF5_INSTRUMENT)
+  set (HDF5_INSTRUMENT FALSE)
+endif()
+
 set (BUILD_TYPE_PROFILE FALSE)
 set (BUILD_TYPE_RELEASE FALSE)
 set (BUILD_TYPE_RELWITHDEBINFO FALSE)
```

You can save this in a file and use `hg import <filename>` to apply it!

update.description:
The HDF5 tools to dump data into h5 file are added. 

The instrument is [commented](https://bitbucket.org/rosebudflyaway/gazebo/src/0ee521b1ccb60f67c7f16e183302a8c7f25705cb/deps/opende/src/quickstep_util.h?at=hdf5_bpmd#cl-50) out by default, to test the data collection, uncomment the two line [here](https://bitbucket.org/rosebudflyaway/gazebo/src/0ee521b1ccb60f67c7f16e183302a8c7f25705cb/deps/opende/src/quickstep_util.h?at=hdf5_bpmd#cl-49). 

For a quick test, `$ gazebo  ..../gazebo/worlds/friction_demo.world` would save a file named `ode_frames.hdf5` in the same directory where you run this command. 

Another quick test would be `$ ..../test/regression/REGRESSION_351_world_step`.
update.title: HDF5 instrument tool integrated
